    }, 
    {
        "text": "History of Hahoe Folk Village", 
        "line": 4, 
        "range": [
            442, 
            470
        ], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 5, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "Hahoe Folk Village was the birth place of two famous historical figure, Ryu Unrong and Ryu Seongryong. Both were blessed with immense talent, one was a Confucian scholar during the Joseon Dynasty, while the other one was the Prime Minister when the Japanese invaded South Korea.", 
        "line": 6, 
        "range": [
            472, 
            749
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    474, 
                    492
                ], 
                "name": "Hahoe Folk Village"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 7, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "The name itself means \u201cRiver Returning\u201d where the location of the village is right near the bend of the S shape Nakdong River. In the eastern part of the village, a small mountain named Mountain Hwa stands 271 meters high.", 
        "line": 8, 
        "range": [
            751, 
            976
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    820, 
                    827
                ], 
                "name": "village"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
