    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 11, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "The moment I stepped into the world heritage site, the weather was cloudy and misty. Sometimes the sky started to cry, and stopped, and cried again.", 
        "line": 12, 
        "range": [
            1006, 
            1153
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1033, 
                    1056
                ], 
                "name": "the world heritage site"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 13, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "Usually I didn\u2019t like getting wet at all but turned out the rain has create an idyllic tone of the village itself.", 
        "line": 14, 
        "range": [
            1155, 
            1270
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1256, 
                    1263
                ], 
                "name": "village"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 15, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "I immediately took a small boat crossing the Nakdonggang river then climbed to the top of Buyongdae Cliff until I found the astounding view of Hahoe Folk Village.", 
        "line": 16, 
        "range": [
            1272, 
            1433
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "TRANS_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1300, 
                    1304
                ], 
                "name": "boat"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LINE_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    1318, 
                    1335
                ], 
                "name": "Nakdonggang river"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    1363, 
                    1378
                ], 
                "name": "Buyongdae Cliff"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    1416, 
                    1434
                ], 
                "name": "Hahoe Folk Village"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 17, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "The Pungsan Ryu clan who formed the village was one of the five powerful local familie of the Andong region which produced many notable politicians and scholars.", 
        "line": 18, 
        "range": [
            1435, 
            1595
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1473, 
                    1480
                ], 
                "name": "village"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    1531, 
                    1544
                ], 
                "name": "Andong region"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 19, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "The houses of Yangban Nobility are mostly made by timber-framed with tiled roofs, while commoners built houses of mud over timer framework and the roofs were thatched with rice straw.", 
        "line": 20, 
        "range": [
            1597, 
            1779
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "FAC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1604, 
                    1630
                ], 
                "name": "houses of Yangban Nobility"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "FAC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1704, 
                    1710
                ], 
                "name": "houses"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 21, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "Complemented with irrigated rice paddies on the slope of the mountain, this landscape has never been more refreshing than the others.", 
        "line": 22, 
        "range": [
            1781, 
            1913
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    1813, 
                    1825
                ], 
                "name": "rice paddies"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
